div.div: On Windows, the AdbWinApi libraries (AdbWinApi.dll and AdbWinUsbApi.dll) need to be installed into locations where Windows will be able to pick them up. The simplest way to achieve that is to install them into the same directory the primary executables (adb, fastboot) are in. The nativefiles/release_configuration_standardlayout.ini native file enforces this.
